snippet.textDisplay:
I hope everyone is confused about what the official video is representing to us.. let me explain it to you. So we got 3 guys and 2 ladies in the video. 
Video starts when annural was feeling cold and maanu gave her the red scarf then scene changes when Maanu holds the red scarf and started singing while getting into the train he dropped the scarf outside (prolly to put away the memories cuz he's heartbroken) then he sits in the train and the scene changes to past 0:46 when he remembers about a night.
Both mannu and annural are singers at a night club, annural kept the red scarf with her all the time as a sign of love. There's a guy in kurta shalwar (who's probably the manager or organizer) he left the annurals room when maanu was entering, there was a clear tension on maanu's face seeing that guy (he was jealous of that guy). Maanu and annural are smiling together 1:15 representing a good relationship. 
Then there's a third guy wearing grey coat who's secretly into annural and is jealous of both of maanu and annural relation. In club he get bumped to a girl(golden earring girl) girl got deep expressions on her face and knew that the grey suited guy is upto no good. The grey suited guys is  maanu's friend and has guessed the tension on maanu's face when that manager whispers with annural. 2:22  So he thought of a cunning plan he took the red scarf of annural 2:56  and put in the room of that manager. Maanu went to the room having photograph of that manager and depicted the wrong idea. 3:22 . 
Annural saw maanu leaving and went to see him then the golden earring girl came and told her about what happened. She ran for Maanu to clear the misunderstanding, when maanu dropped the scarf and get into the train, annural came out of the train and picked up the scarf.

snippet.textDisplay:
It's amazing to see this song finally getting the recognition it deserves after almost 9 months of its release.

It became my instant favourite when I listened to it for the first time 10 months ago. I didn't get it. Why is it not getting trendy? Why don't people see the beauty of it. I have kept listening to it almost twice a day, every single day since then. And now seeing 160M views on this......I couldn't be happier.
